com.nokia.places.request

Interface PlaceRequest

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Request

    public interface PlaceRequest
extends Request
    This interface defines a request which is used to obtain in-depth information about a single location.

    The following query retrieves the details of a specified Place
         PlaceRequest.getPlace(placeId)

    • Method Detail

      • getPlace

        Place getPlace(ApiLink id)
               throws java.io.IOException,
                      ServiceError
        This method makes a request for in-depth information about a single location. The call to RESTful Places service is made synchronously, and therefore blocks further operations until the request is complete.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the place
        Returns:
        Full details about a place.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - IOException on I/O errors
        ServiceError - on service errors

      • getPlace

        void getPlace(ApiLink id,
            PlaceRequestListener listener)
        This method makes a request for in-depth information about a single location. The call to RESTful Places service is made asynchronously. It is not blocking.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the place
        listener - a pair of callback functions, one of which shall be called once the request has completed. The listener contains either the result of the request or the error should one occur.
